    {
      "text": "A 45-year-old man reports pain, tenderness, and redness of both pinnae of the ears for the past 10 days. He has been treated with cephalexin for the past 7 days without improvement. Similar episodes, occurring five times during the past year, have been intermittently treated with antibiotics. Yesterday, for the first time, his right eye became red and painful. He also reports occasional joint pain — for example, his right ankle was painful last week, and his left knee is stiff and painful this week. He also notes nasal pain but no fevers, headaches, neck stiffness, focal weakness, cough, epistaxis, mouth ulcers, or skin changes other than on the ears.\nOn examination, he has a temperature of 37.4°C, a heart rate of 82 beats per minute, and a blood pressure of 125/82 mm Hg. Both ears are swollen and tender (figure). Hearing in the left ear is diminished. The bridge of the nose is tender, but the mucosa of the anterior nasal cavity is normal. His right eye is injected with prominent, tortuous vessels, but his vision is intact. His left knee is warm with a moderate effusion.\nLaboratory testing reveals normal electrolyte levels, kidney function, and blood counts. Tests of blood culture, HIV infection, serum glucan, and treponemal antibody are negative.\nAn antinuclear antibody test is positive at a dilution of 1:80 (reference range, negative at 1:40 dilution) with a homogeneous pattern. Tests for antineutrophil cytoplasmic antibody, rheumatoid factor, and anti-citrullinated protein antibody are negative. A chest radiograph is normal.\nWhich one of the following diagnoses is most likely in this case?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Relapsing polychondritis"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Behçet disease"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Systemic lupus erythematosus"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Sarcoidosis"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Syphilis"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 1,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) CORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_80563&anker=Z0b2aae11adb87ff3ec8e3655c60ebd25\" data-learningcard-id=\"_80563\" data-anker=\"Z0b2aae11adb87ff3ec8e3655c60ebd25\" data-sememe-id=\"AvcRce0\">Relapsing polychondritis</a> is an inflammatory disease characterized by recurrent inflammation in <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7o04WS&anker=Zde961151d845714430b6e0600d08840e\" data-learningcard-id=\"7o04WS\" data-anker=\"Zde961151d845714430b6e0600d08840e\" data-sememe-id=\"TJb6tu\">cartilaginous</a> tissues. The <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=dp0ooS&anker=Z8dd8e7823b54e8fa23ebef7581c7073d\" data-learningcard-id=\"dp0ooS\" data-anker=\"Z8dd8e7823b54e8fa23ebef7581c7073d\">ears</a> are affected most often (sparing the lobule, which does not contain <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7o04WS&anker=Zde961151d845714430b6e0600d08840e\" data-learningcard-id=\"7o04WS\" data-anker=\"Zde961151d845714430b6e0600d08840e\" data-sememe-id=\"TJb6tu\">cartilage</a>), but the nose, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ap0QLS&anker=Zf4e46fc2988b6146686e641dedf19964\" data-learningcard-id=\"ap0QLS\" data-anker=\"Zf4e46fc2988b6146686e641dedf19964\" data-section-id=\"Nvc-Ze0\">trachea</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ap0QLS&anker=Z57eac32cdd516510bce5eb7b1625454d\" data-learningcard-id=\"ap0QLS\" data-anker=\"Z57eac32cdd516510bce5eb7b1625454d\" data-section-id=\"Nvc-Ze0\">bronchi</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Bo0zVS&anker=Z42dfc5649a4025fa49ffc6ebd8712c18\" data-learningcard-id=\"Bo0zVS\" data-anker=\"Z42dfc5649a4025fa49ffc6ebd8712c18\">joints</a> are also frequently affected. Inflammation in the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=dp0ooS&anker=Zacf763e3a9c068642d39ad3c7037de20\" data-learningcard-id=\"dp0ooS\" data-anker=\"Zacf763e3a9c068642d39ad3c7037de20\" data-section-id=\"HDcKfe0\" data-sememe-id=\"nwX7jZ0\">inner ear</a> can cause <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=6j0jYT&anker=Zfe658db52a5746f3d7ff8c015f217b6a\" data-learningcard-id=\"6j0jYT\" data-anker=\"Zfe658db52a5746f3d7ff8c015f217b6a\">hearing loss</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=wn0hvg&anker=Z2031dfc529753af06643e25abc560651\" data-learningcard-id=\"wn0hvg\" data-anker=\"Z2031dfc529753af06643e25abc560651\" data-sememe-id=\"6K0jhS\">tinnitus</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=fH0kph&anker=Z14d3256dfcfa77a52c215adc98335d7a\" data-learningcard-id=\"fH0kph\" data-anker=\"Z14d3256dfcfa77a52c215adc98335d7a\" data-sememe-id=\"AR0Rpf\">vertigo</a>. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=dp0ooS&anker=Z8dd8e7823b54e8fa23ebef7581c7073d\" data-learningcard-id=\"dp0ooS\" data-anker=\"Z8dd8e7823b54e8fa23ebef7581c7073d\">Ear</a> inflammation is commonly mistaken for infection but fails to respond to <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\">antibiotics</a>. Systemic <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=fT0kJ2&anker=Z65c5d02013e50d4a2715ee8ae8d47b02\" data-learningcard-id=\"fT0kJ2\" data-anker=\"Z65c5d02013e50d4a2715ee8ae8d47b02\" data-sememe-id=\"iP0JeT\">vasculitis</a> involving vessels of any size can be seen. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=KO0UtT&anker=Zc1e820388c82ae048336657d20831b79\" data-learningcard-id=\"KO0UtT\" data-anker=\"Zc1e820388c82ae048336657d20831b79\" data-section-id=\"FwXgkZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"QVXu8C\">Episcleritis</a> is common, but patients should be evaluated for the presence of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=KO0UtT&anker=Z768cc0a8261d2703c0592372b33f0a50\" data-learningcard-id=\"KO0UtT\" data-anker=\"Z768cc0a8261d2703c0592372b33f0a50\" data-section-id=\"8wXOkZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"EM08qg\">scleritis</a>, which can be <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=cp0aoS&anker=Z8473446b734702b73ac2972b7bbf7bf7\" data-learningcard-id=\"cp0aoS\" data-anker=\"Z8473446b734702b73ac2972b7bbf7bf7\" data-section-id=\"Dvc1Xe0\" data-sememe-id=\"fm1kUh0\">vision</a> threatening. Patients with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_80563&anker=Z0b2aae11adb87ff3ec8e3655c60ebd25\" data-learningcard-id=\"_80563\" data-anker=\"Z0b2aae11adb87ff3ec8e3655c60ebd25\" data-sememe-id=\"AvcRce0\">relapsing polychondritis</a> can experience abnormalities of cardiac conduction, leading to life-threatening <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7S04af&anker=Ze688ba61de47d1456aee769e72c55a4c\" data-learningcard-id=\"7S04af\" data-anker=\"Ze688ba61de47d1456aee769e72c55a4c\" data-sememe-id=\"Yk0nmT\">arrhythmias</a>.<br><br>The findings in this case could also represent <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=TT06J2&anker=Z25d11f8e1a305f5eaf4caa32877882f3\" data-learningcard-id=\"TT06J2\" data-anker=\"Z25d11f8e1a305f5eaf4caa32877882f3\" data-sememe-id=\"QP0ueT\">granulomatosis with polyangiitis</a> (<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=TT06J2&anker=Z25d11f8e1a305f5eaf4caa32877882f3\" data-learningcard-id=\"TT06J2\" data-anker=\"Z25d11f8e1a305f5eaf4caa32877882f3\" data-sememe-id=\"QP0ueT\">GPA</a>; formerly referred to as Wegener’s). Therefore, the diagnosis of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=TT06J2&anker=Z25d11f8e1a305f5eaf4caa32877882f3\" data-learningcard-id=\"TT06J2\" data-anker=\"Z25d11f8e1a305f5eaf4caa32877882f3\" data-sememe-id=\"QP0ueT\">GPA</a> should be considered, especially because long-term treatments differ for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=TT06J2&anker=Z25d11f8e1a305f5eaf4caa32877882f3\" data-learningcard-id=\"TT06J2\" data-anker=\"Z25d11f8e1a305f5eaf4caa32877882f3\" data-sememe-id=\"QP0ueT\">GPA</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_80563&anker=Z0b2aae11adb87ff3ec8e3655c60ebd25\" data-learningcard-id=\"_80563\" data-anker=\"Z0b2aae11adb87ff3ec8e3655c60ebd25\" data-sememe-id=\"AvcRce0\">relapsing polychondritis</a>. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=TT06J2&anker=Z25d11f8e1a305f5eaf4caa32877882f3\" data-learningcard-id=\"TT06J2\" data-anker=\"Z25d11f8e1a305f5eaf4caa32877882f3\" data-sememe-id=\"QP0ueT\">GPA</a> is a <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=fT0kJ2&anker=Z65c5d02013e50d4a2715ee8ae8d47b02\" data-learningcard-id=\"fT0kJ2\" data-anker=\"Z65c5d02013e50d4a2715ee8ae8d47b02\" data-sememe-id=\"iP0JeT\">vasculitis</a> associated with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ul0pAT&anker=Z3f8c855e1ccc3466ab76aac3acdd6556\" data-learningcard-id=\"ul0pAT\" data-anker=\"Z3f8c855e1ccc3466ab76aac3acdd6556\" data-section-id=\"ACXRuZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"LYYwpn\">antineutrophil cytoplasmic antibodies</a> (<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ul0pAT&anker=Z3f8c855e1ccc3466ab76aac3acdd6556\" data-learningcard-id=\"ul0pAT\" data-anker=\"Z3f8c855e1ccc3466ab76aac3acdd6556\" data-section-id=\"ACXRuZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"LYYwpn\">ANCA</a>), but <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ul0pAT&anker=Z3f8c855e1ccc3466ab76aac3acdd6556\" data-learningcard-id=\"ul0pAT\" data-anker=\"Z3f8c855e1ccc3466ab76aac3acdd6556\" data-section-id=\"ACXRuZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"LYYwpn\">ANCA</a> testing may be negative in patients with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=TT06J2&anker=Z25d11f8e1a305f5eaf4caa32877882f3\" data-learningcard-id=\"TT06J2\" data-anker=\"Z25d11f8e1a305f5eaf4caa32877882f3\" data-sememe-id=\"QP0ueT\">GPA</a> limited to the upper (extrathoracic) <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ap0QLS&anker=Z5a964768554f93e7967999032fda236f\" data-learningcard-id=\"ap0QLS\" data-anker=\"Z5a964768554f93e7967999032fda236f\">airway</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=cp0aoS&anker=Zc03d1938acead6d505567a38bbc70fe6\" data-learningcard-id=\"cp0aoS\" data-anker=\"Zc03d1938acead6d505567a38bbc70fe6\" data-section-id=\"_vc5ce0\" data-sememe-id=\"xtXEf-\">orbits</a>, periorbital <span data-sememe-id=\"T4c6ic0\">soft tissue</span>, nasal <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7o04WS&anker=Zde961151d845714430b6e0600d08840e\" data-learningcard-id=\"7o04WS\" data-anker=\"Zde961151d845714430b6e0600d08840e\" data-sememe-id=\"TJb6tu\">cartilage</a> (with saddle-nose deformity), and auditory systems. Distinguishing such cases of “limited” <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=TT06J2&anker=Z25d11f8e1a305f5eaf4caa32877882f3\" data-learningcard-id=\"TT06J2\" data-anker=\"Z25d11f8e1a305f5eaf4caa32877882f3\" data-sememe-id=\"QP0ueT\">GPA</a> from <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_80563&anker=Z0b2aae11adb87ff3ec8e3655c60ebd25\" data-learningcard-id=\"_80563\" data-anker=\"Z0b2aae11adb87ff3ec8e3655c60ebd25\" data-sememe-id=\"AvcRce0\">relapsing polychondritis</a> can be difficult. The presence of renal involvement with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ng07D2&anker=Z9c5f8677487e73a816c65d200fde1c66\" data-learningcard-id=\"ng07D2\" data-anker=\"Z9c5f8677487e73a816c65d200fde1c66\" data-section-id=\"LRdwnp0\" data-sememe-id=\"yKcdQW0\">pauci-immune glomerulonephritis</a> should point to <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=TT06J2&anker=Z25d11f8e1a305f5eaf4caa32877882f3\" data-learningcard-id=\"TT06J2\" data-anker=\"Z25d11f8e1a305f5eaf4caa32877882f3\" data-sememe-id=\"QP0ueT\">GPA</a> as the cause of symptoms.<br><br><span class=\"wichtig\"><b>Key learning point:</b></span> Recurrent episodes of inflammation involving the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=dp0ooS&anker=Z8dd8e7823b54e8fa23ebef7581c7073d\" data-learningcard-id=\"dp0ooS\" data-anker=\"Z8dd8e7823b54e8fa23ebef7581c7073d\">ears</a>, nose, and/or respiratory tract, along with ocular inflammation, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=dv0o_3&anker=Z52319437e83ee150fa73e1c4fa94ee4f\" data-learningcard-id=\"dv0o_3\" data-anker=\"Z52319437e83ee150fa73e1c4fa94ee4f\" data-section-id=\"wOdhuJ0\" data-sememe-id=\"1hV2180\">polyarthritis</a>, and audiovestibular involvement, are characteristic of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_80563&anker=Z0b2aae11adb87ff3ec8e3655c60ebd25\" data-learningcard-id=\"_80563\" data-anker=\"Z0b2aae11adb87ff3ec8e3655c60ebd25\" data-sememe-id=\"AvcRce0\">relapsing polychondritis</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>Behçet disease is a multisystem inflammatory condition that features recurrent oral and genital <span data-sememe-id=\"SAcyQU0\">ulcers</span> in virtually all cases. Patients often experience ocular disease, including panuveitis. Features of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=fT0kJ2&anker=Z65c5d02013e50d4a2715ee8ae8d47b02\" data-learningcard-id=\"fT0kJ2\" data-anker=\"Z65c5d02013e50d4a2715ee8ae8d47b02\" data-sememe-id=\"iP0JeT\">vasculitis</a> are variably present; <span data-sememe-id=\"8SVOY80\">chondritis</span> occurs in a very small percentage of cases.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=sk0t6T&anker=Z9ead07ca260935bfb60db0d6dca6587d\" data-learningcard-id=\"sk0t6T\" data-anker=\"Z9ead07ca260935bfb60db0d6dca6587d\" data-sememe-id=\"2M0TLg\">Syphilis</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=dT0op2&anker=Zc038efa4f85b330e4a8d1d0224d5f1a9\" data-learningcard-id=\"dT0op2\" data-anker=\"Zc038efa4f85b330e4a8d1d0224d5f1a9\" data-sememe-id=\"6q0jzS\">systemic lupus erythematosus</a> do not typically involve the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=dp0ooS&anker=Z8dd8e7823b54e8fa23ebef7581c7073d\" data-learningcard-id=\"dp0ooS\" data-anker=\"Z8dd8e7823b54e8fa23ebef7581c7073d\">ears</a> in this manner.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Mh0Mef&anker=Zbc455d0c75c00212699a0ab1837deb19\" data-learningcard-id=\"Mh0Mef\" data-anker=\"Zbc455d0c75c00212699a0ab1837deb19\" data-sememe-id=\"Hk0K6T\">Sarcoidosis</a> is a systemic granulomatous disease that can have a wide range of manifestations. However, inflammation of the pinnae and absence of hilar <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=iL0Jxg&anker=Z9a24d08ab67dee43098222189f24cc1a\" data-learningcard-id=\"iL0Jxg\" data-anker=\"Z9a24d08ab67dee43098222189f24cc1a\" data-sememe-id=\"OCYIHr\">lymphadenopathy</a> are both unusual.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=sk0t6T&anker=Z9ead07ca260935bfb60db0d6dca6587d\" data-learningcard-id=\"sk0t6T\" data-anker=\"Z9ead07ca260935bfb60db0d6dca6587d\" data-sememe-id=\"2M0TLg\">Syphilis</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=dT0op2&anker=Zc038efa4f85b330e4a8d1d0224d5f1a9\" data-learningcard-id=\"dT0op2\" data-anker=\"Zc038efa4f85b330e4a8d1d0224d5f1a9\" data-sememe-id=\"6q0jzS\">systemic lupus erythematosus</a> do not typically involve the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=dp0ooS&anker=Z8dd8e7823b54e8fa23ebef7581c7073d\" data-learningcard-id=\"dp0ooS\" data-anker=\"Z8dd8e7823b54e8fa23ebef7581c7073d\">ears</a> in this manner.</div>",
